  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with major orthopedic surgery will be recruited. Participants will be monitored for
      delirium after surgery. Participants' blood will be harvested for the determination of
      haptoglobin types, levels of oxidative stress and inflammation. Investigators will then
      analyze the data to see if haptoglobin 2-2 type is associated with an increased postoperative
      delirium, inflammation and oxidative stress.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
